on & Mobile Screens<br>Offers 3-Types of Interfaces</p>\r\n         </td>\r\n         <td style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all;\">\r\n            <p align=\"center\">[Play Support]<br>A function that performs hunting on your<br>behalf according to the options you set.</p>\r\n         </td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n   </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>', '/upload/2021\\09\\13/002_1.jpg', 'false', 'false'),
(9, 'Play Support System', '<p 맑은=\"\" 고딕\",=\"\" \"malgun=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" \"microsoft=\"\" jhenghei\",=\"\" meiryo,=\"\" \"ms=\"\" pgothic\",=\"\" 돋움,=\"\" dotum,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(73, 73, 73); font-family: \"맑은 고딕\", \"Malgun Gothic\", AppleSDGothicNeo-Light, \"Noto Sans CJK KR\", Dotum, 돋움, \"Microsoft NeoGothic\", \"Droid sans\", sans-serif;\"><font style=\"font-size: 20px !important;\">A convenience system that supports players in various situations such as hunting and combat.</font></p><p 맑은=\"\" 고딕\",=\"\" \"malgun=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" \"microsoft=\"\" jhenghei\",=\"\" meiryo,=\"\" \"ms=\"\" pgothic\",=\"\" 돋움,=\"\" dotum,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(73, 73, 73); font-family: \"맑은 고딕\", \"Malgun Gothic\", AppleSDGothicNeo-Light, \"Noto Sans CJK KR\", Dotum, 돋움, \"Microsoft NeoGothic\", \"Droid sans\", sans-serif;\"><br></p><p 맑은=\"\" 고딕\",=\"\" \"malgun=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" \"microsoft=\"\" jhenghei\",=\"\" meiryo,=\"\" \"ms=\"\" pgothic\",=\"\" 돋움,=\"\" dotum,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(73, 73, 73); font-family: \"맑은 고딕\", \"Malgun Gothic\", AppleSDGothicNeo-Light, \"Noto Sans CJK KR\", Dotum, 돋움, \"Microsoft NeoGothic\", \"Droid sans\", sans-serif;\">The Play Support System (PSS), which was only available in the Event Hunting Grounds, has been officially adopted in the remaster.<br>Players can adjust options such as attack, recovery, buffs, and hunting grounds to suit their playstyle, and continue hunting even when they have to leave the PC for a long time.</p><p 맑은=\"\" 고딕\",=\"\" \"malgun=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" \"microsoft=\"\" jhenghei\",=\"\" meiryo,=\"\" \"ms=\"\" pgothic\",=\"\" 돋움,=\"\" dotum,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(73, 73, 73); font-family: \"맑은 고딕\", \"Malgun Gothic\", AppleSDGothicNeo-Light, \"Noto Sans CJK KR\", Dotum, 돋움, \"Microsoft NeoGothic\", \"Droid sans\", sans-serif;\"><br></p><div class=\"wiki__h2\" 맑은=\"\" 고딕\",=\"\" \"malgun=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" \"microsoft=\"\" jhenghei\",=\"\" meiryo,=\"\" \"ms=\"\" pgothic\",=\"\" 돋움,=\"\" dotum,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" medium;\"=\"\" style=\"font-family: \"맑은 고딕\", \"Malgun Gothic\", AppleSDGothicNeo-Light, \"Noto Sans CJK KR\", Dotum, 돋움, \"Microsoft NeoGothic\", \"Droid sans\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\r\n<h2>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"13812-1\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__h2\"></div>\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"><font color=\"#ed1c24\">ALT +W </font></span>You can open the PSS options window to set potion registration, hunting patterns, etc., and activate PSS directly with ALT +G.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n</h2>\r\n<h2>Basic Functions</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"13812-2\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__h2\"></div>\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/76/98/67e4be64895a30db5fb2d094.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p>In the main tab on the top right, you can choose from three modes: All, Support, and Base.</p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">All (Repeat Hunting Function)</span></p>\r\n         <p>Character moves on its own &#11116  hunts &#11116  returns &#11116  purchases &#11116  storage.<font color=\"#ed1c24\"> Long-term hunting mode</font>.</p>\r\n         <span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"></span>\r\n         <p><br><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Support (auto-buff function in battle)</span></p>\r\n         <p>Hunting and PVP are controlled by the player.<font color=\"#ed1c24\"> A mod that automatically uses potions and buffs.</font></p>\r\n         <span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"></span>\r\n         <p><br><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Base (hunting function around the base)</span></p>\r\n         <p>Hunt monsters around your <font color=\"#ed1c24\">character and doesn\'t teleport in base hunting mode</font><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">.</span></p>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n</h2>\r\n<h2>Essential settings for character protection</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"13812-3\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__h2\"></div>\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n         <p align=\"left\">There are settings that are essential to protect your character from attacks from other players or unexpected situations that occur in the hunting ground.</p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Departure Conditions</span></p>\r\n         <p align=\"left\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/63/34/0305766d6556182c89f40dcf.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"></p>\r\n         <div align=\"left\"></div>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p>It is set in the main tab at the top of the options window, in order to prevent the character from dying while moving to the hunting ground. <font color=\"#ed1c24\">HP 80% or higher is safe to set up.</font></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Return Conditions</span></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\r\n         <p><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/39/19/5111dd639b45e54f76d286b0.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"><br></p>\r\n         <p>Set in the Attack tab at the top of the options window, it will automatically return when HP drops below a certain number or when the number of potions and teleport scrolls falls below a certain number. At this time, if you don\'t have a return scrolls in your inventory, you won\'t return and will continue hunting, so be sure to <font color=\"#ed1c24\">bring return scrolls with you</font>.</p>\r\n         <p><br><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Teleport Conditions</span></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\">\r\n            <p></p>\r\n            <p></p>\r\n         </div>\r\n         <p><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/32/57/d916dc2840930ac8f3bc8a45.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"><br></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\r\n         Set in the Route Tab at the top of the options window and teleports according to certain conditions. If you set the HP or lower setting to high in an area with a lot of monsters, you will be able to teleport infinitely, so be careful. And in areas where teleportation is not possible, teleportation does not work.\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <table class=\"custom-table\" style=\"clear: both; width: 1260px; table-layout: fixed;\">\r\n            <tbody>\r\n               <tr>\r\n                  <td class=\"box2 width600\" ..=\"\" img=\"\" powerbook=\"\" icon-noti.png\");=\"\" background-size:=\"\" 23px=\"\" 23px;=\"\" background-position:=\"\" 20px=\"\" background-repeat:=\"\" no-repeat;\"=\"\" style=\"padding: 22px 25px 20px 50px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all; background-color: rgb(254, 251, 246); background-image: url(\"\");\">\r\n                  <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">HOT TIP!</span></p>\r\n                  <p>If you set the non-combat time of the teleport conditions shorter, you can increase the efficiency of hunting.</p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n               </tr>\r\n            </tbody>\r\n         </table>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n</h2>\r\n<h2>Buff Items and Magic Settings</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"13812-4\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__h2\"></div>\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n         <p>By selecting the Buff Tab you can set various buff items and buff magic.</p>\r\n         <p>Too add to the registration window, drag it from the inventory or magic window double-click to add it. </p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Buff - Fixed</span></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\">\r\n            <div class=\"img_right\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 50px; float: right; text-align: right;\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/73/49/96ad7cef07a2e367015aacf3.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\"></div>\r\n         </div>\r\n         Register various buff items such as haste potions, food, and scrolls.  Only items that have been identified with a identify scroll can be registered and used.\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <table class=\"custom-table\" style=\"clear: both; width: 1260px; table-layout: fixed;\">\r\n            <tbody>\r\n               <tr>\r\n                  <td class=\"box2 width600\" ..=\"\" img=\"\" powerbook=\"\" icon-noti.png\");=\"\" background-size:=\"\" 23px=\"\" 23px;=\"\" background-position:=\"\" 20px=\"\" background-repeat:=\"\" no-repeat;\"=\"\" style=\"padding: 22px 25px 20px 50px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all; background-color: rgb(254, 251, 246); background-image: url(\"\");\">\r\n                  <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">HOT TIP</span></p>\r\n                  <p>You can only use battle scrolls, experience potions, dragon jewels, dishes and soups can be registered.</p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n               </tr>\r\n            </tbody>\r\n         </table>\r\n         <br>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Buff-Freedom</span></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\">\r\n            <div class=\"img_right\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 50px; float: right; text-align: right;\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/50/81/2ac4b00fd980867aa0520f71.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\"></div>\r\n         </div>\r\n         You can freely set the buff skills and extra buff items that each class can use.\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p>For the buff skill settings for each class, you can refer to the examples at the bottom of the page and modify them to suit your playstyle.<br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Setting up Recovery Items</span></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\">\r\n            <div class=\"img_right\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 50px; float: right; text-align: right;\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/50/14/432b14546071ace87cbcb8ec.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\"></div>\r\n         </div>\r\n         Use potions when HP/MP falls below a certain value, and use the registered item at 0 rank when it drops to that value.\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <table class=\"custom-table\" style=\"clear: both; width: 1260px; table-layout: fixed;\">\r\n            <tbody>\r\n               <tr>\r\n                  <td class=\"box2 width600\" ..=\"\" img=\"\" powerbook=\"\" icon-noti.png\");=\"\" background-size:=\"\" 23px=\"\" 23px;=\"\" background-position:=\"\" 20px=\"\" background-repeat:=\"\" no-repeat;\"=\"\" style=\"padding: 22px 25px 20px 50px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all; background-color: rgb(254, 251, 246); background-image: url(\"\");\">\r\n                  <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">HOT TIP</span></p>\r\n                  <p>If you set a powerful health recovery to 20% HP and a health recovery to 80% HP, you will use a powerful health recovery at 1%~20% HP, and a health recovery agent at 21%~80% HP.</p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n               </tr>\r\n            </tbody>\r\n         </table>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\">\r\n            <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Polymorph and Other Items</span></p>\r\n         </div>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images simg\" style=\"clear: both;\">\r\n            <div class=\"img_right\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 50px; float: right; text-align: right;\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/46/89/ae7e5c9a5d5ab4c65029ec48.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\"></div>\r\n         </div>\r\n         For polymorph settings, click on the polymorph monster image to bring up a list of polymorph, where you can click on the polymorph you want. In addition, you can also register Magic Doll Summon and Antidote items, as well as Eva\'s Blessing items.\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p>To use the polymorph function, you need a polymorph spell book, and to summon a magic doll, you need a crystal (the polymorph control ring cannot be used, but transformation using the polymorph control ring is possible).</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n</h2>\r\n<h2>Setup spells for battle</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"13812-5\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__h2\"></div>\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n         <p>In the battle tab, you can set magic to be used sequentially on monsters and magic that matches HP & MP conditions.</p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images dimg\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px; clear: both;\">\r\n            <div class=\"img1\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n               <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/34/32/e685e62862d575da395704ae.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n               <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">Attack Skill - Sequential Example</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"img2\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 10px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n               <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/34/32/a0eab2ebc9ab21750268698a.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n               <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">Attack Skills - Examples of Conditions</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n         </div>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Attack Skill - Sequence</span></p>\r\n         <p>Use the spell you set on the monster 1 time in order.</p>\r\n         <p>For example, if you set it as pictured, it will cast 1 Mana Drain and then 6 Turn Undead on a monster.</p>\r\n         <p><br><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Attack Skill-Condition</span></p>\r\n         <p>Each class can set its magic according to its HP and MP settings to increase its hunting retention.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n</h2>\r\n<h2>Setup Hunting Ground/Move To</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"13812-6\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__h2\"></div>\r\n      <div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n         <p>In PSS, you can set your own route to the hunting area, and you can also teleport directly to the recommended hunting grounds.</p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images dimg\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px; clear: both;\">\r\n            <div class=\"img1\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n               <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/28/35/93d0b650312150c9beddb87b.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n               <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">After setup, turn on the path movement options!</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"img2\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 10px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n               <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/28/35/8921807244c97b0880201005.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n               <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">It\'s convenient to save your route</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n         </div>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <div class=\"images dimg\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px; clear: both;\"></div>\r\n         <p></p>\r\n         <p>- You can use the save button (in the form of recording) near the NPC in the warehouse, then manually move the character and stop at the desired hunting spot before saving.<br>- Typical hunting grounds are set by default to recommended hunting grounds, so they can be used immediately without saving routes.<br>- You can store up to 10 hunting grounds.<br>- When moving, a Blessed Teleportation Scroll or Tower of Arrogance Movement Scroll is required.</p>\r\n         <p><br></p>\r\n         <table class=\"custom-table\" style=\"clear: both; width: 1260px; table-layout: fixed;\">\r\n            <tbody>\r\n               <tr>\r\n                  <td class=\"box2 width600\" ..=\"\" img=\"\" powerbook=\"\" icon-noti.png\");=\"\" background-size:=\"\" 23px=\"\" 23px;=\"\" background-position:=\"\" 20px=\"\" background-repeat:=\"\" no-repeat;\"=\"\" style=\"padding: 22px 25px 20px 50px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all; background-color: rgb(254, 251, 246); background-image: url(\"\");\">\r\n                  <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">HOT TIP!</span></p>\r\n                  <p>It\'s safer to hunt monsters when traveling a route (if you have a saved route with combat enabled while moving), you can save money on potions by setting a village with a low tax rate as a return town.<br></p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n               </tr>\r\n            </tbody>\r\n         </table>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n</h2>\r\n</div>', '/upload/2021\\09\\13/002_18.jpg', 'false', 'false');
INSERT INTO `app_powerbook` (`id`, `title`, `content`, `mainImg`, `main`, `guideMain`) VALUES
(10, 'PC Room Premium', '<div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"17165-0\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans KR&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; padding-top: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__body\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n      <p style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><font size=\"2\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Special services only available in PC Rooms</font></p>\r\n      <p style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n      <p style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Characters who play or log in to &lt;Lineage&gt; at Lineage-affiliated PC cafes will&nbsp;receive a Pixie\'s&nbsp;Golden Feather, which can be used to enjoy various services.</p>\r\n   </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"17165-1\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans KR&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__h2\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n      <h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans KR&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Pop-ups for PC Room</h2>\r\n   </div>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__body\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><img src=\"https://assets.playnccdn.com/gamedata/powerbook/lineage/84044c825a098ce4b819a4fe.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" alt=\"\" style=\"border-style: none; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"></div>\r\n      By pressing the PC button above or entering the command (/pc), a pop-up for PC cafes will appear.\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n         With the second update, the pop-up window has been revamped so that you can see more benefits/rewards at a glance.<br style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n         <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><br style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><img src=\"https://assets.playnccdn.com/gamedata/powerbook/lineage/2a600384b0c630c84beab887.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" alt=\"\" style=\"border-style: none; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"></div>\r\n   </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"17165-2\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans KR&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;\">\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__h2\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n      <h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans KR&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">PC Room Buff</h2>\r\n   </div>\r\n   <div class=\"wiki__body\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><img src=\"https://assets.playnccdn.com/gamedata/powerbook/lineage/81b768b7190f8ac453ee6d1d.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" alt=\"\" style=\"border-style: none; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"></div>\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><br style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"></div>\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">With the 24th Anniversary Update, new buffs have been added for PC Room.</div>\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">You can find Fidor, the mysterious Enchant Mage, or pay for Pixie\'s Golden Feather in the PC Room Play Master pop-up window to receive a village buff. &nbsp;22. 12. 7. In the 2nd PC Room benefit update, \'Pixie\'s Golden Buff\' has been added.</div>\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><br style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"></div>\r\n      <div style=\"letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">\r\n         <table class=\"custom-table\" style=\"clear: both; w