고딕\",=\"\" \"malgun=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" \"microsoft=\"\" jhenghei\",=\"\" meiryo,=\"\" \"ms=\"\" pgothic\",=\"\" 돋움,=\"\" dotum,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" medium;\"=\"\">\r\n<div class=\"wiki__h2\">\r\n   <h2>How to Enter</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n   <p>- Forgotten Island is open from 09:00 to 18:00 on weekends (Sat/Sun).<br>- At 18:00 everyone is teleported to Heine Village.<br>- Forgotten Island is accessible by boat from Heine Docks, and avaiable at level 85+.<br>- When returning to the mainland, you can talk to the teleporter on Forgotten Island.</p>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n   <table class=\"custom-table\" style=\"clear: both; width: 1260px; table-layout: fixed;\">\r\n      <tbody>\r\n         <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all;\">\r\n               <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/43/39/841f355af94af7bf5a208152.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all;\">\r\n               <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/26/47/1de73e6d8f08387c73db3e06.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all;\">\r\n               <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/96/16/2a67bbda49886dd9f5f0b251.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n         </tr>\r\n         <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all;\">\r\n               <p align=\"center\">Weekends 09:00 ~ 18:00<br>1hr boat ride from Heine Docks</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all;\">\r\n               <p align=\"center\">Isbal the Dock Manager<br>Purchase \'Boat Ticket\'</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all;\">\r\n               <p align=\"center\">Return to Mainland<br>Talk to teleporter</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n         </tr>\r\n      </tbody>\r\n   </table>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div><div class=\"wiki__group\" id=\"16515-3\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" 맑은=\"\" 고딕\",=\"\" \"malgun=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" \"microsoft=\"\" jhenghei\",=\"\" meiryo,=\"\" \"ms=\"\" pgothic\",=\"\" 돋움,=\"\" dotum,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" medium;\"=\"\">\r\n<div class=\"wiki__h2\">\r\n   <h2>Layout</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"wiki__body\">\r\n   <p>Forgotten Island is a hunting ground which is only available during certain times, allowing you to gain much more experience points then other hunting grounds.<br>The difficulty level of monsters that appears varies depending on the area, monsters of level 92+ spawns on this island.</p>\r\n   <p><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/50/50/5372649196c5a119b0d546f0.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"></p>\r\n   <p><br></p>\r\n   <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">(1) Hunting Ground Features</span><br>- Gain high experience points at a hunting ground that is only available on weekends (Sat/Sun) 09:00~18:00.<br>- PSS not available.<br>- Random teleportation and no return (die and restart in Heine town upon restart)<br>- There is day and night, and at night, powerful monsters and a large number of monsters appear around the character.<br>- Day and night vision unique to the Forgotten Island.<br>- The Forgotten Isles will cause poisoning in some areas at a certain time, and HP will decrease over time.<br>- The difficulty of the monsters that appear is divided according to the zone.</p>\r\n   <p><br></p>\r\n   <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">(2) Main system</span><br>By hunting normal monsters and boss monsters, you can aim to obtain legendary weapons and various spellbooks in addition to new items.</p>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n   <div class=\"images dimg\" style=\"clear: both; margin-bottom: 30px;\">\r\n      <div class=\"img1\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n         <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/34/63/6e06f825e2759dc2eb179b1e.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n         <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">Obtain new items through regular monster hunting.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"img2\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 10px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n         <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/34/63/b1b632c808f81e6bf7cbd912.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n         <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">Through bosses, you can get new items and legendary weapons.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n   <p><br></p>\r\n   <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">1) Day/Night</span><br>- On the Forgotten Island, there are monsters that only appear at night, unlike during the day.<br>- At night, a large number of monsters appear around the user, so it is expected that a tense hunt will be required.</p>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n   <div class=\"images dimg\" style=\"clear: both; margin-bottom: 30px;\">\r\n      <div class=\"img1\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n         <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/84/24/d5898bc0f58debc90be52ecd.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n         <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">A total of 14 types of night-only monsters, such as bugbears</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"img2\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 10px; max-width: 340px; float: left;\">\r\n         <img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/84/24/f2b78c8dc15affa05888ecce.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\">\r\n         <p class=\"caption\" style=\"padding-top: 6px; max-width: 340px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4;\">At night, a large number of monsters appear around the user.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n   </div>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n   <p><br></p>\r\n   <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">2) Poisoned areas</span></p>\r\n   <p><img src=\"https://wstatic.plaync.co.kr/powerbook/lineage/33/90/bb3bf6bc6aaf8358389a57dc.jpg\" class=\"upimg\" style=\"border-style: none;\"></p>\r\n   <p><br></p>\r\n   <p>- At a certain time, poisoning occurs randomly in a specific area and HP is continuously reduced.<br>- Since it is impossible to prevent poisoning with antidotes, items, or skills, it appears that a high level of difficulty will be required when quickly escaping from the area or hunting.</p>\r\n   <p><br></p>\r\n   <p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">3) Forgotten Items</span><br>- You can get new items by defeating monsters on the Forgotten Island.<br>- In addition to weapons/skills, new items can also be used to create breath and spell books, so it is expected that many users of the Forgotten Island will participate.</p>\r\n   <p></p>\r\n   <table class=\"custom-table\" style=\"clear: both; width: 1260px; table-layout: fixed;\">\r\n      <tbody>\r\n         <tr>\r\n            <td class=\"box1\" style=\"padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(239, 239, 239); word-break: break-all; background-color: rgb(244, 245, 247);\">\r\n               <p align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Material<